In 1996, she passed the "qualified vocal artist" examination organized by TRT ([[Turkish Radio and Television Corporation]]) and started work as a contract Turkish folk singer. She acted and sang the role of Amber in the [[Yunus Emre]] Musical staged at [[AtatÃ¼rk Cultural Center]] in 1997. In 1998, she published her album, ''Avuntu'' (Consolation), the product of 15 months' work. In the same year, she played a lead role with [[TarÄ±k Akan]] in her first [[feature film]], ''[[EylÃ¼l FÄ±rtÄ±nasÄ±]]'' (September Storm), directed by [[AtÄ±f YÄ±lmaz]].
